<head>ARMOUR</head>
    <list type="translations">
        <item xml:lang="zh">甲冑</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">

    <p resp="#CH" modified="2020-11-06T19:42:25.253+09:00">DEFENSIVE WEAPONS to SAFEGUARD one's BODY IN-RELATION-TO ATTACK. </p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>[GENERAL/SPECIFIC]</p>
<p>1. The dominant general term is jiǎ 甲 and this armour is typically made of rhinoceros leather.</p>
<p>[GENERAL]</p>
<p>2. Jiè 介 is another common, and syntactically flexible, word for armour.</p>
<p>3. Kǎi 鎧 refers to metal plate armour.</p>
<p>[SPECIFIC]</p>
<p>4. Xuán jiǎ 玄甲 refers to iron plate armour.</p>
<p>[SPECIFIC]</p>
        </div>
<div type="huang-jingui">
<p>HUANG JINGUI 2006 WARFARE 20.</p>
<p>甲，皮甲；護衛衣總稱。</p>
<p>鎧，鐵甲，鐵護身衣通稱。</p>
<p>胄，甲士戴的護頭衣，即頭盔。</p>
<p>兜鍪，專稱鐵護頭衣。</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>裝甲</p>
<p>盔甲</p>
